The measures - which include compulsory or recommended confinement, curfews and quarantines - are in place in more than 90 countries and territories. PARIS, France - More than 3.9 billion people, or half of the world's population, are now being called on to remain in their homes to combat COVID-19, according to an AFP tally on Thursday. The measures -- which include compulsory or recommended confinement, curfews and quarantines -- are in place in more than 90 countries and territories. The introduction of a curfew in Thailand, which takes effect on Friday, pushed the number past half of the global population. For official information about COVID-19 from the Department of Health, please visit sacoronavirus.co.za